line_1: And others, like your humble servan',
line_2: Poor wights! nae rules nor roads observin;

line_1: And others, like your humble servan',
line_2: To right or left, eternal swervin,

line_1: And others, like your humble servan',
line_2: Till curst with Age, obscure an' starvin,

line_1: An' think na, my auld, trusty Servan',
line_2: That now perhaps thou's less deservin,

line_1: An' think na, my auld, trusty Servan',
line_2: An' thy auld days may end in starvin',

line_1: An' think na, my auld, trusty Servan',
line_2: A heapet Stimpart, I'll reserve ane
